Kim Jong Il Sends Message of Condolences to Hu Jintao 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent a message to Hu Jintao, General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, on Saturday expressing condolences over the death of illness of Huang Ju, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the CPC and vice-premier of the State Council. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon hearing the sad news that Huang Ju, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the CPC and vice-premier of the State Council, died of illness to our sorrow, I express deep condolences to you and, through you, to the CPC and the bereaved families of the deceased. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Huang Ju devoted himself to the cause of building a modern socialist society of Chinese characteristics under the leadership of the CPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has made a great contribution to boosting the DPRK-China friendship as a close friend. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exploits performed by him for the Party and people of China and the development of DPRK-China friendly relations will last forever.

70th Anniversary of Victory in Pochonbo Battle Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hyesan, June 3 (KCNA) -- A national meeting to mark the 70th anniversary of the victory in the historic Pochonbo battle commanded by President Kim Il Sung was held on the ground in front of the Monument to the Victorious Battle of Pochonbo on June 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Yong Chun, Choe Thae Bok, Kim Ki Nam and Choe Yong Rim, leading officials of the Party and military organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army, officials in the field of the preservation of revolutionary sites, science, education, culture and art and media, heroes, those who had the honor of being received by the President, persons of merit, members of the June 18 construction shock brigade and officials and working people in Ryanggang Province and Hyesan City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok, alternate member of the Political Bureau and secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pochonbo battle commanded by Kim Il Sung on June 4, Juche 26 (1937) explicitly told the whole world that the Korean people were not dead but alive and clearly proved the truth of the unique revolutionary idea of attaching importance to arms that fighting against the aggressors with arms alone makes it possible to achieve the sovereignty and independence of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The brilliant victory in the Pochonbo battle also taught the whole world the truth that the people deprived of their country can surely emerge victorious only when they fight against the aggressors, thus greatly encouraging the world revolutionary people in their struggle for national liberation and anti-imperialist, anti-fascist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The victory in the operations for advancing into the homeland including the Pochonbo battle made the august name of the President serve as a beacon for the national resurrection for all the Korean people and the trust and reverence of the whole Korean nation for the President rapidly grew more profound.  Thanks to the leadership of the President the Korean people dynamically turned out in the anti-Japanese resistance, with the firm faith that Korea was sure to gain independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pochonbo battle recorded a shining place in the history of the Korean people's anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle as it was an event of significance which proved the truth that a people guided by an outstanding leader can emerge victorious in the confrontation with any formidable imperialist enemies if they struggle to carve out the destiny of the country and the nation with the arms of revolution in their hands, proceeding from the firm independent stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fighting spirit displayed in the Pochonbo battle and exploits performed during the battle made great contributions to enriching the revolutionary traditions of Mt. Paektu and serve as a source of strength and a firm foundation which enable the WPK and the Korean people to advance the revolutionary cause of Juche along the road of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to these glorious revolutionary traditions the army and people of the DPRK could defeat the brigandish Japanese imperialists, accomplish the historic cause of the country's liberation and successfully build a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They put an end to the history of national subjugation and sufferings and covered a victorious road of independence, the path of socialism under the leadership of the President. With Kim Jong Il at the helm of the revolution, they are now creditably burnishing the new era of Juche revolution, the era of Songun, demonstrating the spirit of socialist Korea to the world on the glorious path of upholding his experienced and seasoned Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the firm will and determination of the WPK to steadfastly carry forward and develop the revolutionary traditions of Juche established by the President and dynamically advance the revolutionary cause of Songun based on the great traditions no matter how the times and situation and conditions of the revolutionary struggle may change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called upon all the servicepersons and people to single-mindedly unite around Kim Jong Il and resolutely fight for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, the country's reunification and the final victory of the revolutionary cause of Juche.

Functions Held in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- Lectures, photo exhibitions and film shows took place in Austria, Brazil and Laos in the period from May 24 to 28 on the occasions of the 43rd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 7th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were photos showing the exploits of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean films including the "Landscape of the country taking more beautiful appearance under the leadership of the great General", "Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks."

DPRK Women's Eleven Beats Australian Rival 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- An Asian regional women's football qualifier between the DPRK team and the Australian team belonging to Group B was held at the Yanggakdo Football Stadium in Pyongyang Sunday for the 29th Olympic Games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK team trounced the Australian rival 2:0.

Congratulations to Syrian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Saturday sent a congratulatory message to Bashar Al-Assad on his reelection as President of Syria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said that his reelection as president of Syria is an expression of absolute support of the Syrian Arab people to his energetic activities and devotional efforts to build an independent and prosperous country and defend the sovereignty and dignity of the Arab nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Availing himself of the opportunity to express belief that the traditional ties of friendship, cooperation and solidarity between the two countries would continue to grow stronger in the future, too, Kim in the message sincerely wished the Syrian president good health and happiness and greater success in his responsible work.

New Buildings of Koryo Songgyungwan Academy to Be Constructed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kaesong, June 2 (KCNA) -- New buildings of Koryo Songgyungwan Academy, which boasts its more than 1,000 year-long history as a time-honored educational and cultural heritage of the Korean nation, are now under construction in parallel with the old buildings of the Academy standing at the foot of picturesque Mt. Songak in Kaesong, a time-honored cultural hub. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new buildings with a total floor space of tens of thousands of square meters will have three or four storied main buildings of Korean architectural style, a gymnasium, an outdoor swimming pool, a practice shop and appendixes.

Message of Condolences to Chinese Premier of State Council 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Kim Yong Il sent a message to Wen Jiabao, premier of the State Council of China, expressing condolences over the death of illness of Huang Ju, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and vice-premier of the State Council. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed deep condolences to the Chinese premier and, through him, to the Chinese government and the bereaved family of the deceased. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Huang Ju devotedly worked for the development of the CPC and China and the happiness of the Chinese people, the message said though he passed away, his exploits will last long.

Security Authorities' Crackdown upon Protesters under Fire in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the All-People Movement for Checking the south Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement reportedly called a press conference in Seoul on May 30 to denounce the security authorities for their suppression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference assailed the security authorities for issuing subpoenas not only to members of the leadership of the headquarters but to some cadres and members of its affiliated organizations in different fields and areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the security authorities of pressurizing members of the organization to pay damages under all sorts of pretexts, the press release branded such reckless action as a sinister move to check the people's actions against the conclusion of FTA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press release demanded the security authorities immediately stop their suppression and violent acts against the people protesting against FTA.

Japan's Moves to Rewrite "Pacifist Constitution" Denounced in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification and other civic and public organizations of south Korea reportedly called a press conference in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul to denounce the Japanese authorities for working hard to revise the "Pacifist Constitution" on May 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference said that the constitutional revision would only encourage the revived Japanese militarist forces in their efforts to turn Japan into a military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said that the main purpose sought for by Japan through the constitutional revision is to remove the mechanism banning the exercise of the "right to collective self-defense" and realize its wild ambition for the reinvasion of Korean Peninsula at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation will never pardon the Japanese reactionaries' constitutional revision, the press release warned, calling upon all the patriotic people of different social standings on this land to join the Japanese people in their dynamic struggle against it.

Full-Scale Actions for Repeal of NSL Declared in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for the Repeal of "National Security Law (NSL)" grouping more than 300 civic and public organizations and political parties of different circles in south Korea reportedly held a meeting of representatives in Seoul on May 29 to declare full-scale actions for the repeal of the evil law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization accused the security forces of their evermore undisguised suppression as evidenced by the "case of the single-minded association" and the arrest of Ri Si U. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization declared it would set the period from June to December as a period of the campaign for the repeal of the NSL and conduct diverse mass movements to have the evil law repealed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization said that as an immediate action it would ensure that the commemoration of the 20th anniversary of the June popular resistance marks an important occasion in the above-said campaign.

Angolan Military Delegation Feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- A reception was hosted by the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces on Saturday for the Angolan military delegation on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were members of the delegation led by Kundi Paihama, minister of Defense. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, in a speech at the reception said that boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Angola is in line with the desire and aspiration of the two armies and peoples and is of weighty significance in ensuring peace and security in the region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that views on boosting the exchange and cooperation between the two armies would be exchanged and their interaction would produce good results during the visit of the delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Angolan minister of Defense said in a speech that the Angolan people have a firm will to boost the friendly and cooperative relations with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Conveying the thanks of the Angolan government to the DPRK government for the sincere assistance given during the difficult period, the minister noted that the friendly relations between the two countries provided by President Kim Il Sung are now growing stronger under the leadership of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed hope that the Korean people would achieve greater success in the future.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Angolan Defense Minister
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the Angolan minister of Defense on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, by Kundi Paihama, minister of Defense, on Saturday.

U.S. moves to Impose Financial Burden upon S. Korea under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification reportedly held a press conference in front of the building of the Ministry of National Defence in Seoul on May 31 to accuse the U.S. of forcing south Korea to cover the expenses for the disposal of its reserve war materiel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the press conference said that negotiations are now under way between the authorities of south Korea and U.S over the issue of disposing of the U.S. reserve war materiel, noting that they are aimed at realizing Washington's intention to free itself from the burden of covering the expenses for the disposal of large quantities of reserve war materiel stockpiled in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They termed the U.S. assertion that the transfer of the reserve war materiel to the south Korean army would result in cutting down the above-said expenses by 1.3 billion USD is little short of a blatant call for bringing all the burdens for that purpose upon the shoulders of the south Korean side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Assailing the military authorities for taking a humiliating negotiating posture, they strongly demanded the Ministry of the National Defence turn down the pressure for covering the above-said expenses.

June 15 Era of Reunification Sure to Triumph under Kim Jong Il's Leadership
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The cause of national independence and the cause of the country's reunification are sure to emerge victorious thanks to the leadership of Kim Jong Il over the movement for national reunification as all Koreans single-mindedly revere him as a peerless patriot, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 joint declaration was a great fruition of Kim Jong Il's noble idea of national independence, his energetic leadership over the movement for national reunification and broad magnanimity based on patriotism, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic Pyongyang meeting and the June 15 joint declaration brought about the phase of historic turning point in which the north and the south advance towards reconciliation, unity and independent reunification through national cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now all Koreans in the north, the south and abroad are waging a dynamic struggle to achieve the independent reunification, regarding "By our nation itself" as their common idea of reunification, irrespective of ideology and ism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il expounded the idea of giving importance to arms, the idea that peace and security of the country and the destiny of the nation are guaranteed by the force of arms, trained the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK into invincible armed forces and provided powerful war deterrent for self-defence firmly guaranteeing peace on this land. By doing so, he gave steady continuity to the June 15 era of reunification and enabled not only the people in the north but also the fellow countrymen in the south to live in peace, benefited from the Songun politics. Thanks to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, peace on the Korean Peninsula has been firmly protected and the national history is making steady advance towards reconciliation and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il kindly invites whoever stands for national reunification with national conscience to join the ranks of Koreans keen to achieve great national unity, be he a capitalist, an army general or one in the upper crust of the ruling quarters.  This all-embracing policy based on patriotism serves as a key driver in the era of national reconciliation and unity, the June 15 era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is, indeed, a great leader of the nation who enjoys the high authority amid the unanimous respect and boundless praise from all Koreans in the north, the south and abroad irrespective of ideology and system as he has made immortal contributions to the sacred patriotic cause for the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are still many difficulties and obstacles in the way of national reunification. However, the Korean nation is firmly convinced of the victory of the June 15 era of reunification.

Imperialists' Ideological and Cultural Poisoning Accused
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The imperialists' moves for capitalistic ideological and cultural poisoning are their vicious counter-revolutionary ideological offensive aimed at benumbing the sound thinking and consciousness of people and destabilizing and degenerating the anti-imperialist independent countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists are keen to spread capitalist idea and culture in a bid to wipe out the revolutionary thinking and consciousness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is their calculation that they can not only make their ideology and culture prevail over the whole world but easily win over the people of progressive countries and realize their wild ambition to dominate the world if they effectively use their reptile media without resorting to the force of arms. For this reason, they spend an increasing amount of money every year for boosting the number of reptile media, sharply boosting the quantities of propaganda materials and making them more reactionary and obscene in their contents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the propaganda materials produced by the imperialists are without exception most reactionary as they diametrically run counter to progressive ideology and culture and play a very harmful role. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their moves for ideological and cultural poisoning adversely affect the struggle of the people for independence against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle against imperialism precisely means a showdown between forces and ideologies. It is impossible to advance revolution and protect the gains of revolution already achieved unless people are equipped with progressive thought and get working class awareness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle against the capitalist ideological and cultural poisoning means fierce confrontation with imperialists and a struggle to defend the country's sovereignty without gunfire. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will thoroughly frustrate the imperialists' vicious capitalist ideological and cultural poisoning with a high degree of revolutionary vigilance, firmly defend the socialist political and ideological position and thus powerfully accelerate the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, the article concludes.

Wreath Placed at Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 3 (KCNA) -- The Angolan military delegation led by Kundi Paihama, minister of Defense, laid a wreath at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the wreath-laying music, the wreath in the name of the delegation was laid at the cemetery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the wreath were letters "Glory to the Revolutionary Martyrs!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests paid silent tribute to the revolutionary martyrs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They placed bouquets before the bust of Anti-Japanese War Hero Kim Jong Suk before observing a moment's silence.

Kim Jong Il's Leadership Exploits Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- A meeting and book exhibition were held by the Juche Idea Study Society of Delhi of India and a seminar on Kim Jong Il's work "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction" and film show by the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism on May 25 and 26 on the occasion of the 43rd anniversary of his start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the book exhibition were works of Kim Jong Il and books introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 B.C. Gupta, chairman of the above-said Indian society, in his speech at the meeting said that Kim Jong Il formulated the revolutionary idea of President Kim Il Sung as an integral system of idea, theory and method of Juche, set forth a policy of modeling the whole party on the Juche idea and wisely led the work to settle all the issues arising in the Party building and activities as required by the idea and intention of the President and fully meet the needs of the Juche idea in leading the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ramon Jimenez Lopez, president of the Mexican committee, said at the seminar that Kim Jong Il authored many immortal works, making a great contribution to the development of human thought and the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film show watched Korean film "The Great Leader Steering the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation to Victory."

Art Performance Given to Mark Anniversary of Victory in Pochonbo Battle
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pochon, June 1 (KCNA) -- A performance was given by the central art group of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea in Pochonbo on June 1 on the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the victory in the Pochonbo battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance started with chorus "Long Live Generalissimo Kim Il Sung". The group staged a colorful repertoire fully representing the joy of the agricultural workers and other people of the DPRK at marking the 70th anniversary of the victory in the Pochonbo battle commanded by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recitation of full-length epic "Mt. Paektu", female solo and pangchang of the classic masterpiece "Song of Anti-Japanese War," male solo "Pochonbo, Land of Glory", female trio "Arirang that Resounded through Jiansanfeng" and other numbers made the audience recollect with deep emotion victorious battles including the Pochonbo battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Female solo "General's Trip to the Front", mixed duet "Blue Sky over My Country" and other numbers impressively depicted the great exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in powerfully arousing the agricultural workers and other people to the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, holding high the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its repertoire also included chorus "Let's Keep Step with the General's", female chorus "New Spring Has Come", male duet "Boasting Rich Potato Harvest."

International Children's Day Greeted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The Korean children joyfully greeted the International Children's Day on June 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sports and amusement games and colorful art performances of children took place at the nurseries and kindergartens including Kim Jong Suk Nursery and the Changgwang Kindergarten and the Mangyongdae Fun Fair, the Rungra Islet Recreation Ground and other places in Pyongyang that day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The children had a morning exercise and rhythmic exercise to the tune of songs including "Thank You General Kim Jong Il" and "Today is June 1".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their amusement games included flying balloons, walking along other's footprints and planting flags before running back. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Children in the local areas of the country, too, significantly celebrated the day with sports games and art performances.

68th Meeting for Peace and Disarmament Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The 68th meeting for peace and disarmament was reportedly held in front of the building of the Ministry of National Defense in Seoul on May 29 under the sponsorship of the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting accused the U.S. of working hard to force south Korea to cover the expenses to be incurred by the disposal of its reserve war materiel and so on, demanding the U.S. immediately ship back the materiel to its mainland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out at the meeting denounced the above-said ministry for building facilities in Yongdong County, North Chungchong Province to dispose of unusable ammunition of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Asserting that the U.S. should shoulder all the financial burdens related to storing, management and disposal of reserve war materiel, the resolution demanded the immediate nullification of the unequal south Korea-U.S. "memorandum of agreement on unified ammunition aid system".

Greetings to Italian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Saturday sent a message of greetings to Giorgio Napolitano, President of the Republic of Italy, on its national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the friendly relations between the DPRK and Italy would further expand and develop, Kim in his message wished the Italian people new progress and prosperity.

Kim Il Chol Meets Angolan Military Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Saturday met and had a friendly talk with the Angolan military delegation led by Kundi Paihama, minister of Defense. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Vice-Minister of the People's Armed Forces Pak Jae Gyong and KPA generals and officers.

Floral Tribute Paid to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- A military delegation of Angola led by Kundi Paihama, minister of Defense, placed a floral basket before the statue of President Kim Il Sung on Mansu Hill Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music the guests laid a floral basket in the name of its delegation before paying tribute to the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the basket were words "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung will live forever." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A welcome function took place in front of the Monument to the Victorious Fatherland Liberation War after its arrival here Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, and general officers and officers.

Chollima Statue
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- The Chollima Statue was erected in Pyongyang in April Juche 50 (1961), in reflection of the revolutionary mettle of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea which was effecting epoch-making leaps and innovations in the socialist construction.  It has been festooned with lights of a new form, attracting people's eyes when night comes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The concentrated illumination with the close light projection as the main raises the light effect to give an impression of seeing the Chollima (winged horse) flying in the night sky. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new form of illumination is adding beauty to the night view of the city and giving rich emotion and creative enthusiasm to the working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Chollima Statue is inspiring the Korean people in their general march for building a great, prosperous and powerful socialist nation in the Songun era.

Juvenile Sports Schools in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- There are a lot of juvenile sports schools in different parts of the DPRK, which play an important part in sports development of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The schools including Sosong District Juvenile Sports School and Jongju City Juvenile Sports School are selecting schoolchildren with aptitude and physiques appropriate to sports and scrupulously organizing lessons and training suitable to their ages and psychological features. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Athletes of sports schools have proved successful in such international matches as the Pyongyang international wrestling invitation games and Asian juvenile field and track championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The schools are also paying a particular attention to making students acquire perfect basic techniques and improve their special skills. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result, Haeju City Juvenile Sports School set DPRK juvenile records in eight categories at the archery event of the 39th national sports contest of juvenile sports schools and Tongrim County Juvenile Sports School and Chongdan County Juvenile Sports School produced such world-famous weightlifters as Ri Song Hui, Kim Myong Nam and Im Yong Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The schools in North and South Phyongan Provinces and South Hamgyong Province have also brought up thousands of promising athletes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The juvenile sports schools across the country, furnished with full facilities and apparatuses, are making every possible effort to rear talented reserve athletes.

Kim Jong Il Guides Preservation of Revolutionary Sites in Kanggye
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 2 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the field of the preservation of revolutionary sites in Kanggye City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK, and Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his guidance was the Ryudong Revolutionary Site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a historic place where President Kim Il Sung stayed from February 26 to 28, 1953 during the hard-fought Fatherland Liberation War, setting forth a strategic policy on further consolidating the rear and giving strong support to the front to bring earlier the final victory in the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being briefed on the revolutionary site before the monument to the site, Kim Jong Il walked round the historic buildings standing as they were before to acquaint himself in detail with the management and operation of the revolutionary site and education conducted there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that there are many historic sites associated with the sacred revolutionary activities of the President in Jagang Province, he said it is, therefore, necessary to preserve them in their original state and strengthen the education through them to more thoroughly equip the Party members and other working people, servicepersons and school youth and children with the revolutionary idea of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his guidance was the Jagang Provincial Museum of Revolutionary Activities of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Systematically displayed at the museum are historic relics related to dozens of visits paid by him to the province to wisely lead its work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After visiting the museum, Kim Jong Il said that Jagang Province, once called a remote mountainous region unfit for human habitation, turned into people's land of bliss under the wise leadership and deep care of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled to manage and operate the revolutionary museum and intensify the education through it, noting that it is one of the important centers for education to arm the Party members and other working people, servicepersons and school youth and children with the revolutionary idea of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He appreciated a performance given by the Jagang Provincial Art Group.

Kim Jong Il dirige sobre terreno fabricas y empresas en Kanggye
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de junio (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea (PTC) y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, dirigio sobre el terreno fabricas y empresas de la ciudad de Kanggye. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Primeramente, estuvo en la Central Hidroelectrica Juventud No. 2 de Hungju, construida nuevamente como gigantesca creacion de la epoca del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Recorriendo el exterior y el interior de esa planta se entero detalladamente del estado de construccion y de produccion electrica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ver el dique, el embalse convertido en un gran lago artificial, las salas de generadores electricos y de distribucion de energia electrica, expreso una gran satisfaccion de que los constructores levantaron excelentemente esta creacion de eterna duracion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Evaluo altamente los meritos de los miembros de la brigada juvenil y otros constructores de la ciudad diciendo que resulta un gran exito el que ellos culminaron esta obra superando valientemente multiples pruebas con la conviccion en la victoria cierta y el optimismo revolucionario, fundamentados en el lema de "Vivir no para hoy sino para el manana".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Senalo que cuando termine la obra de la Central Hidroelectrica Juventud No. 3 de Hungju, es posible materializar el legado del Presidente Kim Il Sung de producir mucha energia electrica utilizando eficazmente el rico caudal del rio Jangja y presento las tareas para concluir esa obra lo mas pronto posible y elevar incesantemente la eficiencia de las centrales ya construidas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Luego, el Dirigente oriento sobre el terreno la Fabrica de Vino de Kanggye. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Se informo del estado de los equipos y la produccion recorriendo los procesos productivos reestructurados tecnicamente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Dijo que al desarrollar ampliamente el movimiento masivo de innovacion tecnica y establecer el sistema de produccion basado en las materias primas locales, esta fabrica mantiene estrictamente el principio de rentabilidad en la administracion empresarial y afirmo que las experiencias de esta unidad comprobaron con hechos que la ciencia y la tecnica son precisamente la produccion y viceversa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Acto seguido, el Dirigente se dirigio a la Fabrica de Patos de Kanggye, nuevamente construida. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
